cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.CY

This paper discusses the use of machine learning and privacy-preserving techniques to generate synthetic data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also touches on privacy concerns, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the use of large datasets and the need for efficient storage and retrieval could place it in cs.DB (Databases). The focus on algorithm performance and testing could also place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
